1.Setting Up a Repository
Initialize a new Git repository
bash
Copy code
git init
Clone an existing repository
bash
Copy code
git clone <repository_url>
2. Basic Configuration
Set your name
bash
Copy code
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
Set your email
bash
Copy code
git config --global user.email "you@example.com"
3. Staging and Committing Changes
Check the status of your repository
bash
Copy code
git status
Add a single file to staging
bash
Copy code
git add <file_name>
Add all files to staging
bash
Copy code
git add .
Commit changes with a message
bash
Copy code
git commit -m "Commit message"
4. Branching
List all branches
bash
Copy code
git branch
Create a new branch
bash
Copy code
git branch <branch_name>
Switch to a branch
bash
Copy code
git checkout <branch_name>
Create and switch to a new branch
bash
Copy code
git checkout -b <branch_name>
Rename the current branch
bash
Copy code
git branch -m <new_branch_name>
5. Merging and Rebasing
Merge another branch into your current branch
bash
Copy code
git merge <branch_name>
Rebase your branch onto another branch
bash
Copy code
git rebase <branch_name>
6. Pulling and Pushing Changes
Pull changes from the remote repository
bash
Copy code
git pull origin <branch_name>
Push changes to the remote repository
bash
Copy code
git push origin <branch_name>
Set up tracking information and push
bash
Copy code
git push -u origin <branch_name>
7. Undoing Changes
Unstage a file
bash
Copy code
git reset <file_name>
Undo the last commit (keep changes)
bash
Copy code
git reset --soft HEAD~1
Undo the last commit (discard changes)
bash
Copy code
git reset --hard HEAD~1
Restore a file to the last committed state
bash
Copy code
git checkout -- <file_name>
8. Working with Remotes
Add a new remote
bash
Copy code
git remote add <name> <url>
View all remotes
bash
Copy code
git remote -v
Remove a remote
bash
Copy code
git remote remove <name>
9. Viewing History and Logs
Show commit history
bash
Copy code
git log
Show commit history with one-line summaries
bash
Copy code
git log --oneline
Show a specific commit
bash
Copy code
git show <commit_hash>
10. Stashing Changes
Stash uncommitted changes
bash
Copy code
git stash
List stashes
bash
Copy code
git stash list
Apply the latest stash
bash
Copy code
git stash apply
Apply and drop a specific stash
bash
Copy code
git stash pop <stash_id>
11. Git Large File Storage (LFS)
Install Git LFS
bash
Copy code
git lfs install
Track a large file with LFS
bash
Copy code
git lfs track "<file_name>"
Push LFS-tracked files
bash
Copy code
git push origin <branch_name>
12. Git Configurations and Helpers
Check global configuration
bash
Copy code
git config --list
Enable color output in Git
bash
Copy code
git config --global color.ui auto
